    "rawMarkdown": "Thanks for opening this topic and sharing your list, Rustam! It’s definitely motivating to see everyone's progress and the stats from the top solutions.\n\nSeeing these numbers makes me wonder: what would the community think about putting together a shared spreadsheet to track our task-by-task scores? We used a similar approach during last year's code golf competition, and it turned out to be an incredibly useful resource for everyone involved. For reference, here is the sheet we used last year: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/u/1/d/e/2PACX-1vQ7RUqwrtwRD2EJbgMRrccAHkwUQZgFe2fsROCR1WV5LA1naxL0pU2grjQpcWC2HU3chdGwIOUpeuoK/pubhtml/sheet?headers=false&gid=1427788625\n\nAlso, @Tony Li — it’s really great to see you here again! Since I remember you participated in last year's code golf as well, I’d love to hear your thoughts. Do you think a shared sheet like that would be helpful for this competition too?\n\nLet me know what you guys think!",
